summary:
✹ I am a designer and creative strategist working at the intersection of UI and UX. I am a responsible, reliable and proactive person with a can-do mindset. Passionate about equality, future and innovation.

✹ I am an award-winning design thinker committed to creating research-based creative yet practical visuals that shape the digital environment in a way that puts users in the centre of the decisions.

✹ I work in several phases in design process - from user research and wireframes to prototyping and creating pixel perfect end visuals. 

✹ Passionate about psychology of aesthetics and future of decentralised (digital) world.

projects: [{'title': 'HeritageBox - 1st place at HeritageHack', 'date': {'start': {'month': 5, 'day': None, 'year': 2021}, 'end': {'month': 5, 'day': None, 'year': 2021}}, 'description': 'Our HeritageBox solution won the 1st prize at HeritageHack national competition in May 2021. HeritageBox is a modular and mobile wooden unit being inserted within the endangered heritage buildings. Units offer simplified architectural and sustainable answers and possible solutions for housing issues and the lack of vibrant and creative industries in peripheral areas. HeritageBoxes can serve as flats, residences for artists or tourists, co-working places, workshops ...  United with its digital platform, the solution offers an uncomplicated response to a complex problem. In virtue of such an innovative idea, we have been invited and are now taking part in an incubation programme Heritage Lab that offers us full support and mentorship together with former European Social Innovation Award winners.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Iva', 'last_name': 'Lukan', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Product designer - UX/UI'}]}, {'title': 'Urban Academy Mobile square', 'date': {'start': {'month': 2, 'day': None, 'year': 2021}, 'end': {'month': 2, 'day': None, 'year': 2021}}, 'description': 'The Mobile square is a creative spatial intervention that suggests the temporary use of abandoned and forgotten urban spaces.\nThe project won 1st prize at the mentorship programme Urban Academy, which connects municipalities and local creatives working on actual problems in their local communities. The project is conceived as a framework for the education and mentoring of municipal personnel and local creatives on themes related to sustainable design, placemaking, temporary use, and other practices of creative urban renewal.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Iva', 'last_name': 'Lukan', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Product designer - UX/UI'}]}, {'title': 'Bellastock Paris - Artecitya Experimental Masterclass', 'date': {'start': {'month': 5, 'day': None, 'year': 2017}, 'end': {'month': 5, 'day': None, 'year': 2017}}, 'description': 'Created in 2006 within the Architecture school of Belleville, Bellastock is firstly a research platform whose activity relies essentially on the organization of an annual festival, reuniting hundreds of architecture students. Throughout the years, Bellastock has diversified its activity by multiplying its partners with schools, enterprises, local authorities and with all actors concerned within city and territory planning projects. Today, it is an operational association for the establishment and monitoring of innovative architectural projects.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Iva', 'last_name': 'Lukan', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Product designer - UX/UI'}]}]
